Wed Apr 21 2005 Jens Miltner <jum@mac.com>
	* MacCvs 3.3a3:
	- MacCvs now uses cvsnt by default (currently, both cvsnt and cvsgui are included and user can switch back to cvsgui:
	    defaults write org.gnu.MacCvs P_UseCvsnt -boolean false
	  The idea is to get rid of cvsgui once we're confident that cvsnt is working reliably on Mac OS X)
	- Browser now properly updates again after move to trash
	- fixed issues where accidentally dragging files/folders within browser window would open a new browser
	- check whether an existing browser already displays the location before opening a new browser and activate
	  that browser instead if one is found
	- bring application forward when dropping files/folders onto app to open a new browser
	- improved log output speed for large checkouts
	- revamped Import dialog: additional options and CVSROOT input
	- revamped Checkout dialog: additional options and CVSROOT input
	- revamped Update dialog: additional options
	- implemented CProgress callback (used when filtering imports)

